                <p>
                  Compact refrigerators are smaller, portable units often used in dorm rooms, offices, or as secondary refrigerators in households. Due to their size and simplicity, they generally have fewer components that can break down. However, they are still susceptible to common issues such as thermostat malfunctions and condenser coil problems. Because these units are often moved around more frequently, they may experience more wear and tear, leading to potential issues with door seals and leveling. Routine checks of the thermostat settings and cleaning the coils can help ensure their longevity and efficient operation.
                </p>
              </div>

