                <p>Maytag refrigerators are known for their durability and straightforward design, often resulting in lower repair costs compared to more technologically advanced brands. Typical repair expenses might range from <b>$150 to $300</b> for issues like a faulty defrost timer or a broken door gasket. If more extensive repairs are needed, such as replacing the compressor, costs can climb to between <b>$500 and $750</b>. Maytag's reputation for reliability means that serious issues are less common, but when they do occur, the availability of parts and skilled technicians can make repairs more affordable and efficient.</p>

