                <p>Frigidaire refrigerators are popular for their affordability and reliable performance. Repair costs for these models are generally on the lower end of the spectrum, with common repairs such as fixing a malfunctioning thermostat, replacing a water filter, or repairing a door seal costing between <b>$100 and $300</b>. More complex repairs, like those involving the compressor or electronic control systems, might range from <b>$400 to $700</b>. Frigidaire's widespread availability and the ease of finding replacement parts can help keep repair costs manageable, making it a budget-friendly option for many consumers.</p>

