                  <div class="FAQ">
                    <div class="fa">
                      <h3>Why is my gas burner not igniting?</h3>
                    </div>

                    <div class="fa_plus">︾</div>

                    <div class="fa_minus">︽</div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="questions">
                    <p>
                      There could be several reasons why your gas burner is not igniting. Here are some potential causes and solutions:
                    </p>

                    <ol>
                      <li><b>Igniter Issues: </b>The igniter could be faulty or dirty. Clean the igniter and surrounding areas to ensure there's no debris blocking the spark. If cleaning doesn't help, you might need to replace the igniter. An appliance repair service can assist with diagnosing and replacing faulty igniters.</li>
                      <li><b>Gas Supply: </b>Ensure that the gas supply to your stove is turned on and that there are no issues with the gas line. If you suspect a gas supply issue, it's best to contact a professional cooktop repair service.</li>
                      <li><b>Control Knob: </b>Make sure the control knob is set to the correct position for ignition. Sometimes, the knob might be faulty or misaligned, preventing the burner from igniting.</li>
                      <li><b>Burner Cap: </b>Check that the burner cap is properly aligned and seated. If it's not in the correct position, the burner may not ignite.</li>
                      <li><b>Electric Coil Burners: </b>If you have a stove with electric coil burners, ensure that the coils are properly connected and not damaged. A damaged coil can prevent the burner from heating up.</li>
                      <li><b>Spark Module: </b>The spark module controls the ignition of the burners. If this component is faulty, the burners may not ignite. An appliance repair service can diagnose and replace a faulty spark module if needed.</li>
                    </ol>
                    <p>If you've tried troubleshooting these common issues and your gas burner still won't ignite, it might be time to call a professional appliance repair service. They have the tools and expertise to diagnose and fix the problem quickly, ensuring your stovetop is back in working order for your cooking needs.</p>
