                  <div class="FAQ">
                    <div class="fa">
                      <h3>What should I do if I smell gas?</h3>
                    </div>

                    <div class="fa_plus">︾</div>

                    <div class="fa_minus">︽</div>
                  </div>

                  <div class="questions">
                   <p>If you smell gas, it's crucial to take immediate and appropriate action to ensure your safety and the safety of others. Follow these steps:</p>
                   <ol>

                    <li>
                      <b>Do Not Ignite Flames or Sparks:</b>
                      <p>Avoid lighting matches, using lighters, or turning on any electrical switches (including lights, appliances, and phones) as these could ignite the gas.</p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <b>Ventilate the Area:</b>
                      <p>If it's safe to do so, open windows and doors to allow fresh air to disperse the gas.</p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <b>Evacuate:</b>
                      <p>Leave the building immediately. Do not attempt to locate the source of the gas leak yourself.</p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <b>Avoid Using Electronics:</b>
                      <p>Do not use any electronic devices, including cell phones, until you are at a safe distance from the suspected leak. Even a small spark from a phone can ignite gas.</p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <b>Shut Off the Gas Supply:</b>
                      <p>If you know how and can do so safely, turn off the gas supply at the main shutoff valve. This is often located near the gas meter outside your home.</p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <b>Call for Help:</b>
                      <p>Once you are at a safe distance, call your gas company's emergency number or the local fire department to report the gas leak. Use a neighbor’s phone or your mobile phone once you are clear of the building.</p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <b>Do Not Re-enter the Building:</b>
                      <p>Do not go back inside until professionals have declared it safe to do so.</p>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                      <b>Follow Professional Advice:</b>
                      <p>Listen to and follow the instructions provided by emergency personnel and gas company technicians. They will assess the situation and take appropriate action to resolve the gas leak.</p>
                    </li>

                   </ol>
                   <p>Taking these steps promptly can help prevent potentially dangerous situations and ensure everyone's safety.</p>
